body:
### Version

Yosys 0.34+55 (git sha1 672375ed0, clang 14.0.6 -fPIC -Os)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Verilog file `top.v` (very similar to one of the examples in [IEEE 1364-2005](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/servlet/opac?punumber=10779) section 12.2.1):
```verilog
module top;
	wire clk;
	wire [0:4] in1;
	wire [0:4] o1;
	vdff m1(
		.out(o1),
		.in(in1),
		.clk(clk)
	);
endmodule

module vdff (
	out,
	in,
	clk
);
	parameter size = 1;
	input [0:size - 1] in;
	input clk;
	output reg [0:size - 1] out;
	always @(posedge clk) out = in;
endmodule

module annotate;
	defparam top.m1.size = 5;
endmodule
``` 
Run:
```
yosys -p "read_verilog top.v"
```

### Expected Behavior

Successfully finished Verilog frontend.

### Actual Behavior

Yosys failed with:
```
-- Running command `read_verilog top.v' --

1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: top.v
Parsing Verilog input from `top.v' to AST representation.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\top'.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\vdff'.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\annotate'.
top.v:0: ERROR: Can't find object for defparam `top.m1.size`!
```

